[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426517&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426517&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

At UCL we made the decision to have the name resolver deliver the
address which had the least hop counts from the gateway routing
algorithm.  We dumped our gateways routing table and statically added
this info to the code.  There are obviuosly advantages in asking the
gateway (from time to time) about its routes.
There is an ICMP message for this.
The driving force for this was to ensure we obtained the ARPANET
address of the NIC, not the MILNET address.

Robert

